-- BMW Recalls 350,800 Vehicles, Including Rolls-Royce Models, on Brake Fault
-- B y   T o m   L a v e l l
-- 2010-10-01T10:57:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-01/bmw-recalls-350-800-bmw-rolls-royce-vehicles-on-brake-pressure-pump-fault.html
(Corrects spelling of company name in first paragraph.)  Bayerische Motoren Werke AG is
recalling 350,800 BMW-brand and Rolls-Royce models worldwide to
repair a braking-system fault, a spokesman said.  The voluntary recall affects vehicles built from 2002 until
2010 and involves fixing the brake-pressure pump, Frank Strebe,
the spokesman, said today in a phone interview from the Paris
Motor Show.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Tom Lavell at 
 tlavell@bloomberg.net  